# tooling-gh-pr-auto-merge-rebase-squash-fallback — History

## v2.1.0 (2026-05-17)

**Changed by:** Live encounter on HomericIntelligence/ProjectOdyssey PR #5411
**Verification:** verified-ci

### What changed

- Added a new "Verified On" datapoint: ProjectOdyssey PR #5411 (2026-05-17) re-confirms the org-wide rebase-auto-merge rejection 6 days after the v2.0.0 ecosystem sweep. CLAUDE.md in ProjectOdyssey still prescribes `--auto --rebase`; the rebase attempt failed with the standard GraphQL error and `--auto --squash` armed cleanly.
- Added a new "When to Use" bullet: project-level `CLAUDE.md` files may still prescribe `--auto --rebase` and contradict org-level branch protection — trust this skill over project docs for any HomericIntelligence repo.
- No change to the core recommendation (default to `--squash` for HomericIntelligence repos). Bump is minor — same guidance, broader evidence base.

## v2.0.0 (2026-05-11)

**Changed by:** 2026-05-11 HomericIntelligence ecosystem-wide easy-issue sweep (11 PRs across 11 repos)
**Verification:** verified-ci

### What changed

- **Reframed core finding from "some repos" to "ALL HomericIntelligence repos"**: every PR (n=11) opened during the 2026-05-11 ecosystem-wide easy-issue sweep had `--auto --rebase` rejected and `--auto --squash` accepted. The behavior is now treated as universal across the org rather than a per-repo configuration mismatch.
- **Updated recommendation**: Default to `--squash` directly for any HomericIntelligence repo. The `--rebase`-first-then-fall-back pattern is still documented for portability, but is no longer the recommended default within HomericIntelligence.
- Added new "Verified On" rows for the 11 repos: AchaeanFleet, ProjectAgamemnon, ProjectArgus, ProjectCharybdis, ProjectHermes, ProjectKeystone, ProjectMnemosyne, ProjectNestor, ProjectProteus, ProjectScylla, ProjectTelemachy.
- Added a new Failed Attempts row covering the now-stale assumption from the v2.2.0 multi-repo orchestration skill that rebase auto-merge works org-wide except on Myrmidons.
- Documented that `gh api repos/<repo> --jq '.allow_auto_merge'` returns null for non-admin tokens, so pre-flight detection is unreliable for most callers — strengthening the case for unconditionally defaulting to `--squash`.
- Bumped verification level from `verified-local` to `verified-ci` (11 PRs is far above the threshold for CI-observed repeatability).

### Why

Previous version (v1.0.0) was based on 2 PRs in a single repo (Odysseus) and treated rebase rejection as a per-repo quirk. The 2026-05-11 ecosystem-wide easy-issue sweep produced unanimous evidence (11/11 PRs, 11/11 repos) that EVERY HomericIntelligence repo has rebase auto-merge disabled at the repo settings level. This is no longer a mismatch — it is the org-wide default. Skills and agents that hardcode `--rebase` first waste a round-trip on every PR.

Additionally, the related `multi-repo-pr-orchestration-swarm-pattern` skill (v2.2.0) currently asserts that only Myrmidons (and previously AchaeanFleet) have auto-merge issues. The 2026-05-11 sweep falsifies that scoping; this amendment captures the correction so future amendments to that skill can reference the verified evidence here.

